        "id": "FoI0",
        "credit": 0,
        "rule": "No selections made on Q2 and Q3"
      }
    ],
    "notes": "Tag mapping: Q2 correct/statistical = {correct_p_lt_alpha (option 1), ci_excludes_zero (option 2)}; Q2 integration = {large_n_inflates_sig (option 3), sig_vs_prac_distinction (option 4)}; Q2 misconceptions = {p_as_prob_of_claim (option 5), magnitude_only_reasoning (option 6), need_sd_despite_p_given (option 7)}. Q3 integration = {small_percent_diff_threshold (option 1), effect_size_needed (option 2), ci_near_zero_threshold (option 3), decision_context (option 4)}; Q3 misconceptions = {p_confidence_at_least_effect (option 5), sig_implies_large (option 6), typeI_zero_bigN (option 7), tails_change_effect_size (option 8)}. The scoring prioritizes integrated reasoning (FoI4) that coordinates statistical and practical significance and articulates decision implications."
  },
  "note": "Difficulty is held comparable to the CR version by requiring both a correct statistical warrant (p < .05) and integration selections that recognize large-n inflation and practical thresholds. Distractors target common p-value misinterpretations and magnitude-only judgments without statistical inference."
